text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia wilsonii is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Plurinerves. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt and Mid West regions of Western Australia.The low, spreading and wiry shrub typically grows to a height of 0.2 to 0.5 metres (0.7 to 1.6 ft)  and produces yellow flowers.
